# tiny-llm always-on rules

# Philosophy
- Follow the Zen of Python: prefer simple, explicit, modular code. No emojis.

# Package manager
- Use `uv` for all Python commands (for example `uv run ...`, `uv run pytest`).
- Do not use plain `python`, `pip`, or `pytest` directly.

# Python style
- Use modern type hints (for example `str | Path`, not `Union[str, Path]`).


